The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, June 16, 2003 				 Dips that pose a death threat
		 The road dips sharply  at Esplanade, creating an accident risk. Pictures by  Kishor Roy ChowdhuryTapan Kumar Das: There are dips at the crossing of Chittaranjan Avenue and Mahatma Gandhi Road, and again at Esplanade, due to subsidence of the tram tracks. These are death threats and accident risks.																																																													Such dips exist at other spots, too. We have decided to concretise the gutters in a phased manner.
